#vacancy rate per month

#vectors
number_vacancies = c(568, 316, 306, 273, 258, 244, 252, 258, 235, 209, 210, 207) #numerators, july - june
total_positions = c(4179, 4143, 4143, 4125, 4120, 4120, 4121, 4124, 4116, 4105, 4088, 4802)  #denominators, july - june
month = c("July", "August", "September", "October", "November", "December", "January", "February", "March", "April", "May", "June")


#create df
#ref: https://www.reddit.com/r/RStudio/comments/gowfre/how_to_create_a_dataframe_in_rstudio/

new_df <- cbind.data.frame(
                "pc_month" = c("July", "August", "September", "October", "November", "December", "January", "February", "March", "April", "May", "June"),
                "number_vacancies" = c(568, 316, 306, 273, 258, 244, 252, 258, 235, 209, 210, 207), 
                "total_num_positions" = c(4179, 4143, 4143, 4125, 4120, 4120, 4121, 4124, 4116, 4105, 4088, 4802)
                ) %>%
  mutate(vacancy_rate =number_vacancies/total_num_positions) %>%
  mutate(month = pc_month) %>%
  mutate(`Mean Vacancy Rate` = mean(vacancy_rate))

new_df

#put numbers ahead of month name (so plots in order)
new_df$month[new_df$month == "July"] <- "01 Jul"
new_df$month[new_df$month == "August"] <- "02 Aug"
new_df$month[new_df$month == "September"] <- "03 Sep"
new_df$month[new_df$month == "October"] <- "04 Oct"
new_df$month[new_df$month == "November"] <- "05 Nov"
new_df$month[new_df$month == "December"] <- "06 Dec"
new_df$month[new_df$month == "January"] <- "07 Jan"
new_df$month[new_df$month == "February"] <- "08 Feb"
new_df$month[new_df$month == "March"] <- "09 Mar"
new_df$month[new_df$month == "April"] <- "10 Apr"
new_df$month[new_df$month == "May"] <- "11 May"
new_df$month[new_df$month == "June"] <- "12 Jun"
new_df

#-------------------------------------------
#exclude July
new_df_exclude_july <- cbind.data.frame(
                "pc_month" = c("August", "September", "October", "November", "December", "January", "February", "March", "April", "May", "June"),
                "number_vacancies" = c(316, 306, 273, 258, 244, 252, 258, 235, 209, 210, 207), 
                "total_num_positions" = c(4143, 4143, 4125, 4120, 4120, 4121, 4124, 4116, 4105, 4088, 4802)
                ) %>%
  filter(pc_month != "July") %>%
  mutate(vacancy_rate =number_vacancies/total_num_positions) %>%
  mutate(month = pc_month) %>%
  mutate(`Mean Vacancy Rate` = mean(vacancy_rate))

new_df_exclude_july

#put numbers ahead of month name (so plots in order)
new_df_exclude_july$month[new_df_exclude_july$month == "July"] <- "01 Jul"
new_df_exclude_july$month[new_df_exclude_july$month == "August"] <- "02 Aug"
new_df_exclude_july$month[new_df_exclude_july$month == "September"] <- "03 Sep"
new_df_exclude_july$month[new_df_exclude_july$month == "October"] <- "04 Oct"
new_df_exclude_july$month[new_df_exclude_july$month == "November"] <- "05 Nov"
new_df_exclude_july$month[new_df_exclude_july$month == "December"] <- "06 Dec"
new_df_exclude_july$month[new_df_exclude_july$month == "January"] <- "07 Jan"
new_df_exclude_july$month[new_df_exclude_july$month == "February"] <- "08 Feb"
new_df_exclude_july$month[new_df_exclude_july$month == "March"] <- "09 Mar"
new_df_exclude_july$month[new_df_exclude_july$month == "April"] <- "10 Apr"
new_df_exclude_july$month[new_df_exclude_july$month == "May"] <- "11 May"
new_df_exclude_july$month[new_df_exclude_july$month == "June"] <- "12 Jun"
new_df_exclude_july

#line graph of IDEA Texas vac rate per month - NOT ROUNDED

library(ggplot2)
library(ideacolors)
library(ideadata)


#line graph
#all months- not rounded
l_IDEA_tx_vac_per_month <- new_df %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=month, 
             y= vacancy_rate, 
             #group = Subject, 
             #color = month
             )) +
 geom_point() +
    #scale_color_viridis(discrete = TRUE) +
    #ggtitle("Number of Vacancies for Each Month by Subject") + 
    #theme_ipsum() +
    #ylab("Vacancy Rate SY 23-24")
#geom_line() +
    geom_hline(yintercept = 0.07, color="blue") +
  scale_fill_idea(reverse = FALSE) +
  scale_color_idea() +
  ideacolors::theme_idea_min() +
   #ideacolors::theme_idea_light() +
  #guides(fill = "none", color = "none") +
   theme(legend.position="none") +             #removes legend  (REF:https://r-charts.com/ggplot2/legend/ )
  labs(
    x= "Month",
      y ="Vacancy Rate",
       title = "IDEA Texas Vacancy Rate by Month",
       subtitle = "for Position Control Data SY 23-24") 

l_IDEA_tx_vac_per_month


#excluding July - not rounded
l_IDEA_tx_vac_per_month_exc <- new_df_exclude_july %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=month, 
             y= vacancy_rate, 
             #group = Subject, 
             #color = month
             )) +
 geom_point() +
    #scale_color_viridis(discrete = TRUE) +
    #ggtitle("Number of Vacancies for Each Month by Subject") + 
    #theme_ipsum() +
    #ylab("Vacancy Rate SY 23-24")
#geom_line() +
    geom_hline(yintercept = 0.06, color="blue") +
  scale_fill_idea(reverse = FALSE) +
  scale_color_idea() +
  ideacolors::theme_idea_min() +
   #ideacolors::theme_idea_light() +
  #guides(fill = "none", color = "none") +
   theme(legend.position="none") +             #removes legend  (REF:https://r-charts.com/ggplot2/legend/ )
  labs(
    x= "Month",
      y ="Vacancy Rate",
       title = "IDEA Texas Vacancy Rate by Month",
       subtitle = "for Position Control Data SY 23-24") 

l_IDEA_tx_vac_per_month_exc

#average rate - remove july (twice as large and it’s prior to school starting)


#data
new_df

#average vacancy rate all months (including july)

average_vac_rate_all_months_pc <- new_df %>%
  mutate(`Mean Number of Monthly Vacancies (All Months)` = mean(number_vacancies)) %>%                         #278 (ave numb vacancies/month, all months)
  mutate(`Mean Number of Monthly Total Positions (All Months)` = mean(total_num_positions)) %>%                #4182.12 (ave total numb positions/month, all months)
  mutate(`Mean Monthly Vacancy Rate (All Months)` = mean(vacancy_rate))                                         #0.0667 ave vacancy rate per month, all months
average_vac_rate_all_months_pc

#average vacancy rate all months excluding July - remove july
average_vac_rate_not_july_pc <- new_df %>%
  filter(pc_month != "July") %>%
  mutate(`Mean Number of Monthly Vacancies (Exclude July)` = mean(number_vacancies)) %>%                   #251.64 (ave numb vacancies/month - not july)
  mutate(`Mean Number of Monthly Total Positions (Exclude July)` = mean(total_num_positions)) %>%          #4182.46 (ave total numb positions/month, - not july)
  mutate(`Mean Monthly Vacancy Rate (Exclude July)` = mean(vacancy_rate))                                 #0.0604 ave vac rate (not july)

  average_vac_rate_not_july_pc

  
  
#round to 2 decimals

#all months
average_vac_rate_all_months_pc[,'vacancy_rate']=round(average_vac_rate_all_months_pc[,'vacancy_rate'],2)
average_vac_rate_all_months_pc 
  
average_vac_rate_all_months_pc[,'Mean Number of Monthly Vacancies (All Months)']=round(average_vac_rate_all_months_pc[,'Mean Number of Monthly Vacancies (All Months)'],1)
average_vac_rate_all_months_pc 
 
average_vac_rate_all_months_pc[,'Mean Number of Monthly Total Positions (All Months)']=round(average_vac_rate_all_months_pc[,'Mean Number of Monthly Total Positions (All Months)'],1)
average_vac_rate_all_months_pc
 
average_vac_rate_all_months_pc[,'Mean Monthly Vacancy Rate (All Months)']=round(average_vac_rate_all_months_pc[,'Mean Monthly Vacancy Rate (All Months)'],2)
average_vac_rate_all_months_pc
  

#exclude july
average_vac_rate_not_july_pc[,'vacancy_rate']=round(average_vac_rate_not_july_pc[,'vacancy_rate'],2)
average_vac_rate_not_july_pc

average_vac_rate_not_july_pc[,'Mean Number of Monthly Vacancies (Exclude July)']=round(average_vac_rate_not_july_pc[,'Mean Number of Monthly Vacancies (Exclude July)'],1)
average_vac_rate_not_july_pc  
 
average_vac_rate_not_july_pc[,'Mean Number of Monthly Total Positions (Exclude July)']=round(average_vac_rate_not_july_pc[,'Mean Number of Monthly Total Positions (Exclude July)'],1)
average_vac_rate_not_july_pc
 
average_vac_rate_not_july_pc[,'Mean Monthly Vacancy Rate (Exclude July)']=round(average_vac_rate_not_july_pc[,'Mean Monthly Vacancy Rate (Exclude July)'],2)
average_vac_rate_not_july_pc
